# Rust build artifacts
/target

# Build output. `/dist` is REGENERABLE — `cargo run -p cascade-cli -- dist` reproduces it byte-for-
# byte (verified), so it's a RELEASE artifact (attach to a release), not committed. The spec's source
# of truth (fonts/sources, tokens.ron, …) is what's tracked; dist is derived from it.
/dist

# Build bookkeeping (written into every --out dir)
.cascade-manifest.json
